	<h3 id="thirdthing">Wednesday (music, dance)</h3>


	<p>• <strong>Animal arts (music/dance):</strong> Why not make Wednesday a Darwin-themed, performing-arts day? The children could compose pieces of music based on the movement of different animal species. They could use Camille Saint-Saëns’ <em>Carnival of the Animals</em> as musical inspiration, discussing how the pitch, instrument and pace of the music help to portray each animal. (check out <a href="http://magazines.scholastic.co.uk/resources/27338">‘Aquarium’</a> – an audio poster taken from <em>Carnival of the Animals</em>.) The children could then devise dances based on the animals’ movements or a movement piece using different levels to represent the ‘descent of man’.</p>


